    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed at Model Risk Level 5 for the Class III VAD hemolysis prediction use case. Achieved levels meet or exceed required levels across all factors: software quality assurance (4/4), numerical code verification (4/4), discretization error (4/4), test conditions (3/3), output comparison (4/4), QoI relevance (4/4), validation relevance (4/4), numerical solver error (3/3), use error (3/3), model form (4/4), model inputs (4/4), test samples (3/3), and equivalency of input parameters (3/3). Monte Carlo UQ with 2000 LHS samples documents the 95% CI on the hemolysis index QoI. The CFD model is accepted as credible for predicting absolute hemolysis levels for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under VAD operating conditions at the declared assurance level.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
